  "title": "WORKPLACE SAFETY HEALTH OFFICER",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Enforce compliance with <strong>Workplace Safety and Health Act</strong> and applicable regulations.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site inspections, audits, and risk assessments.</li>\n  <li>Lead investigations into incidents, accidents, and near-misses; recommend and implement corrective actions.</li>\n  <li>Develop and implement workplace safety policies, procedures, and safety programs.</li>\n  <li>Conduct safety briefings, toolbox talks, and training sessions.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and ensure proper use of personal protective equipment (PPE) and safety systems.</li>\n  <li>Prepare reports, maintain safety records, and submit required documentation to regulatory authorities.</li>\n  <li>Act as the key liaison with government agencies (e.g., MOM, NEA, SCDF) on WSH matters.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with OHSAS 18001 / ISO 45001 and ISO 14001</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma in Occupational Safety &amp; Health, Environmental Science, or a related field.</li>\n  <li><strong>Registered WSH Officer with MOM (Singapore)</strong>.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in a WSH role, preferably in construction.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of relevant WSH legislation, codes of practice, and safety management systems (e.g., ISO 45001).</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills; ability to influence and lead safety initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in incident reporting and safety documentation.</li>\n</ul>",
